# Looking for a Chiropractor Near Me in Bandar Rimbayu or Kota Kemuning? Here's What to Know First

If you've searched "chiropractor near me", "chiropractic near me", or "chiro near me" and you're in Bandar Rimbayu, Kota Kemuning, Bandar Saujana Putra, Jenjarom, Telok Panglima Garang, Putra Heights, or anywhere along the ELITE or SKVE corridors, Thrive Gonstead Chiropractic (TGC) is the dedicated Gonstead chiropractic clinic serving this part of Selangor. TGC is built around one system, practised without compromise — and understanding what that system involves will help you know exactly what to expect when you walk in.

---

## Why do people in Bandar Rimbayu and Kota Kemuning search for a chiropractor near them?

Most people searching for a chiropractor or chiropractic care near them are dealing with something specific — lower back pain that won't settle, a neck that locks up after long hours at a desk, or headaches that keep coming back. They want someone nearby who can actually figure out what's going wrong and give them a clear answer.

That's exactly what the Gonstead System is built to do. It's a method of chiropractic assessment that prioritises finding the specific cause before anything else. At TGC, the assessment always comes first. The adjustment follows only when the assessment points clearly to a single level that needs correcting. You get a real answer, not a general one.

---

## What is the Gonstead System and how does TGC practise it?

TGC is a Gonstead-only clinic. Lucas Chong and Ruth Lai both trained at the International Medical University (IMU) in Malaysia and have continued their Gonstead education through the Gonstead Chiropractic Society Australia (GCSA) seminars since 2019. The Gonstead System requires five specific steps before an adjustment is made: instrumentation using the nervoscope, static palpation, motion palpation, visualisation, and X-ray analysis.

Every step adds information. The nervoscope detects asymmetrical heat patterns along the spine — a sign of nerve irritation at that level. Palpation confirms position and movement. X-ray analysis provides structural context. The adjustment only happens when all five findings point to the same level. That level, and only that level, is adjusted with precision.

---

