## What conditions do people come to TGC for?

Patients at TGC present with a wide range of musculoskeletal complaints. The most common include lower back pain, lumbar disc issues, neck pain and cervicogenic headaches, sciatica and radiating leg pain, mid-back stiffness from desk work, and pregnancy-related spinal discomfort. TGC also sees children and infants with postural and developmental concerns.

Chiropractic does not treat disease. What it addresses is spinal subluxation — a joint that has lost normal position or motion, producing nerve irritation at that level. When that subluxation is identified accurately and corrected with a specific adjustment, the nerve that was being irritated functions better. How that improvement shows up depends on what that nerve supplies to the body.

---

## What happens at your first visit at TGC?

Your first visit at TGC takes longer than most people expect. Before any adjustment happens, Lucas or Ruth will take a full case history and conduct a postural examination and nervoscope scan. The nervoscope is a dual-probe instrument that detects heat differential along the spine — an asymmetrical reading at a given level indicates nerve irritation there. If X-rays are clinically indicated, you will be referred for imaging before the adjustment is performed.

First consultations typically run 45 to 60 minutes. The adjustment on your first visit is not given automatically. It is only given if the assessment identifies a clear, specific subluxation to correct. Subsequent visits are shorter, but the assessment is repeated each time because the most involved level can change as your spine responds to care.

---

## Frequently Asked Questions

**I searched "chiropractor near me" in Kota Kemuning. Is TGC close enough?** Yes. TGC in Bandar Rimbayu is approximately 10 to 15 minutes from Kota Kemuning via the ELITE highway. It is one of the closest Gonstead-specific clinics to Kota Kemuning, Bandar Saujana Putra, and the wider Kuala Langat area.

**Do I need to book in advance or can I walk in?** Booking ahead is recommended because the Gonstead assessment takes time and slots fill up. Walk-ins are accommodated when possible, so it's always worth calling ahead to check availability before you make the trip. Bookings can be made through the TGC website or via WhatsApp.

**Is Gonstead chiropractic suitable for children and pregnant women?** Yes. Adjustment technique at TGC is modified based on age, size, and clinical context. Infants receive very light, specific contact. Pregnant patients are assessed and adjusted with positioning adapted for the changed biomechanics of the pelvis and lumbar spine during pregnancy.

**How many visits before I feel a difference?** Acute problems — those that developed within the last few weeks — tend to respond within three to five visits. Chronic conditions that have been present for months or years take longer to stabilise. Visit frequency is guided by your spine's response to care. TGC offers packaged plans for families and for patients who already understand the value of regular maintenance care. And that's something we always encourage. Your health is proactive, not reactive. The best time to care for your spine is before it becomes a problem, not after.

**What makes the Gonstead System specific?** The Gonstead System identifies the single most involved spinal subluxation through a five-step assessment before any adjustment is made. The nervoscope, palpation, visualisation, and X-ray analysis all contribute findings. The adjustment is then directed at one specific level, in a specific direction, based on what that assessment reveals. Every visit starts with the assessment fresh.

